WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.920
Hello everyone, my name is Alvina Gakhokidze and I'm a first year engineering science student at

00:03.920 --> 00:09.600
the University of Toronto and I participated in the ICTC in 2019 and in 2020 and both times I was

00:09.600 --> 00:13.760
in the structural engineering team. The reason I joined the competition in the first place was

00:13.760 --> 00:17.520
because it was on the topic of space which is something I never really learned about in high

00:17.520 --> 00:22.000
school and it was also really exciting to me that scientists didn't know a lot about it either

00:22.000 --> 00:26.320
because we can't really explore outer space like we do the real world. So the whole mystery behind

00:26.320 --> 00:30.640
it was very appealing to me and then the other reason I joined was because I didn't really get

00:30.640 --> 00:35.280
any opportunities in school to apply my scientific knowledge and I liked science so I wanted to be

00:35.280 --> 00:39.040
able to do that and the competition was a great opportunity for that. Because of that I would

00:39.040 --> 00:43.600
really recommend for everyone to try the ICTC especially if you are interested in going into

00:43.600 --> 00:48.000
STEM because it's a great opportunity to a. apply your knowledge and b. also decide if you want to

00:48.000 --> 00:52.240
focus more on theory or practical application which is what helped me the most as well from

00:52.240 --> 00:56.800
the competition. My favorite thing about the ICTC is definitely the people there. I'm still in

00:56.800 --> 01:01.280
contact with volunteers and students that I met. Overall it's just such a unique opportunity

01:01.280 --> 01:04.720
because you get to work with people from all around the world and with different backgrounds

01:04.720 --> 01:08.640
and yet you find that it's pretty easy to communicate and get along because we're all

01:08.640 --> 01:12.480
very driven people and working towards the same goal and this isn't really something that I got

01:12.480 --> 01:16.960
to experience in high school so I was very grateful and it was an unforgettable opportunity.

01:16.960 --> 01:21.360
Lastly the ICTC was the main influence on my university decision because before going into it

01:21.360 --> 01:25.280
I knew that I liked science however I didn't know what I wanted to do with it. But being in the

01:25.280 --> 01:28.880
structural engineering team and being able to design buildings and also look at construction

01:28.880 --> 01:33.680
processes like real engineers do I realized that I really like to build things for humans to use

01:33.680 --> 01:37.920
and so I decided to go into engineering and I've just finished my first semester and I really

01:37.920 --> 01:42.560
enjoyed the program so thank you ICTC so much for helping me figure that out and I know that any

01:42.560 --> 01:46.320
other students who participate in this competition will really enjoy it as well. Yeah thank you

01:46.320 --> 01:52.880
everyone for listening.

